    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "✅ **TO DO #1:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Museum</code> class, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">allExhibitsAbove()</code> method to determine if all exhibits on a given day had more than a target number of visitors. This method should:\r\n1. Take in an integer parameter dayIndex representing the day to check and an integer parameter target representing the minimum number of visitors.\r\n2. Loop through the given column (day) and check if any exhibit had fewer visitors than target.\r\n\t- If at least one exhibit had fewer visitors, return false.\r\n\t- If all exhibits had more than target visitors, return true.\r\n\r\n✅ **TO DO #2:** In the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">MuseumRunner</code> class, call the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black;\">allExhibitsAbove()</code> method with a day index and target visitor number and print the result.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Check out the <strong>Help & Tips</strong> tab ⬆️ for help with traversing a two-dimensional (2D) array in column-major order.\r\n</div>",
